rn&#40;tempbyte&#41;;<br />&#125;<br /></div><br /><br />Why are you setting Tempbyte to something, only to later throw it out?<br />Looks like you are fetching something incorrect for the actual data read out.<br /></div><br /><br />that's because (if i understand correctly) when reading from the area of the PPU memory map with the palette data, that is returned without having a 1-byte buffer delay, but the value is still stored in the buffer.<br /><br />the return(tempbyte) is there instead of return(PPU-&gt;bytebuffer) in case it's a palette read. the palette data can be returned immediately and still get buffered.<br /><br />is this wrong?<br /><br />EDIT: oh i see your first comment there. there is a return(tempbyte) in that if block, it returns that value if the PPU address is under $2000. it's not thrown out.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4572">miker00lz</a> — Wed Feb 22, 2012 2:58 pm</p><hr />
